TITLE: Kentucky police resume manhunt for gunman in I-75 shooting
SUMMARY: Joseph A. Couch, 32, was named a person of interest in the Kentucky shooting, and authorities have said he should be considered armed and dangerous.

TITLE: Georgia shooting suspect's mother called Apalachee High School warning of 'extreme emergency,' aunt says
SUMMARY: Colt Gray's mom said she called Apalachee High School fearing an "impending disaster" and begged staff to check on her son due to an "extreme emergency."

TITLE: Heroism, bravery displayed on 9/11 by plane passengers who made phone calls from hijacked aircraft
SUMMARY: Bravery was displayed in the phone calls made from the hijacked planes on 9/11, which provided critical information to those on the ground.

TITLE: South Carolina inmate lets lawyer choose lethal injection for execution after he was forced to pick method
SUMMARY: A South Carolina inmate forced to choose his execution method left the decision to his lawyer, who picked lethal injection instead of the electric chair or a firing squad.

TITLE: 'Sugar Daddy’ suspect at center of college student's murder probe
SUMMARY: Muna Pandey, 21, was killed in her Houston apartment on August 26. Bobby Singh Shah, 51, was charged in her murder after a tipster recognized him from a 'Sugar Daddy' site.

TITLE: Texas Lyft driver sues rideshare company, hospital after passenger choked him with his own seatbelt
SUMMARY: A Lyft driver who says a passenger choked him with his own seatbelt in Texas earlier this year is suing Lyft and the hospital where he picked up the passenger.

TITLE: Missing Florida runner Arielle Valdes found dead after five-day search
SUMMARY: The body of missing Florida jogger Arielle Valdes was recovered after a five-day search, but police do not suspect foul play in her death.

TITLE: City in Florida providing $1M in opioid settlement money to nonprofits fighting opioid epidemic
SUMMARY: The city of St. Petersburg, Florida, is offering $1 million from an opioid settlement to nonprofit groups working to help combat the opioid crisis.

TITLE: Texas police department to introduce autonomous drone pilot program: 'An eye in the sky'
SUMMARY: One Texas police department is using an "eye in the sky" to help respond to emergency calls after a start-up company created autonomous drones to assist officers.

TITLE: Illegal migrant arrested, accused of rape after being released by Massachusetts court: ICE
SUMMARY: Massachusetts suspect Jorge Luis Castro-Alvarado, a "gotaway" migrant that entered the U.S. without being processed, was arrested and charged with rape, according to ICE.

TITLE: Kentucky police identify subject of manhunt after ‘numerous’ people shot on highway
SUMMARY: Police are searching for a person of interest following a shooting on a highway near London, Kentucky, that left at least seven people injured Saturday evening.

TITLE: Georgia high school shooting: Suspect's former neighbors recount harrowing stories of alleged abuse, chaos
SUMMARY: The former neighbors of the suspected Apalachee High School shooter discussed the Gray family, with neighbors recounting harrowing stories of alleged abuse.

TITLE: Mugshots of the week: Sept. 1-7, 2024
SUMMARY: These mugshots were taken for arrests made throughout the U.S. the week of Sept. 1-7, 2024.

TITLE: Serial killer known as ‘Hollywood Ripper’ extradited to Illinois for 1993 murder of his teen neighbor
SUMMARY: A serial killer who was sentenced to death for the murders of two women in California in 2001 has been extradited to Illinois after being charged with the murder of his former neighbor.

TITLE: Prosecutor of first parents charged in son's school shooting advises Georgia DA to 'have courage'
SUMMARY: The prosecutor behind the very first convictions made against parents of a mass shooter offered the advice "it's not easy" to the legal team for the Georgia high school shooting.

TITLE: Georgia teen school shooting suspect lived in series of rental homes as emerging details shed light on family
SUMMARY: Colt Gray, the teen suspect charged in the Apalachee High School shooting, came from a broken home, with the teen living in at least three rental homes in a short period.

TITLE: NYPD commissioner's brother is ex-cop being probed as alleged 'fixer' for NYC clubs: Report
SUMMARY: NYPD Commissioner Edward Caban's twin, who is a former cop, is being investigated for his alleged work as a "fixer" for restaurants and nightclubs, the New York Post reported.

TITLE: Apalachee High School's district to ramp up security as other students prepare to head back
SUMMARY: Students in Barrow County, Georgia will head back to schools next week with a heightened law enforcement presence in the wake of the Apalachee High School shooting.

TITLE: US Air Force Academy cadet, 19, found dead in dorm room
SUMMARY: The U.S. Air Force Academy says "we lost an incredible teammate" after Cadet 4th Class Avery Koonce of Texas was found dead in her dorm room this week.

TITLE: Karen Read, accused of murdering police officer boyfriend, alleges fellow officers killed him, staged cover-up
SUMMARY: Karen Read, the Massachusetts woman accused of running over her police officer boyfriend and leaving him to die, was interviewed by ABC's "20/20" this week on her recent mistrial.

TITLE: Mental, physical ailments can develop among homeowners overtaken by squatters, according to expert
SUMMARY: When a squatter takes over a property, the home is no longer a safe space for a homeowner. The situation can be traumatic with mental health implications.

TITLE: Memorials honoring 9/11 victims across the United States where you can pay your respects to the fallen
SUMMARY: All around the United States, there are memorials standing tall that honor those whose lives were lost during the terrorist attacks on Sept. 11, 2001.

TITLE: Michigan football player’s Nigerian scammers pay price for teen's sextortion suicide
SUMMARY: Two Nigerian brothers were sentenced in Michigan federal court Thursday to serve 17.5 years in prison for their roles in sextortion crimes that led to 17-year-old Jordan DeMay's suicide.

TITLE: ‘Digital bodyguards’ can help combat criminals targeting victims through social media: expert
SUMMARY: A cybsersecurity expert said influencers and celebrities should have "digital bodyguards" protect their information as criminals use increasingly sophisticated tools to target them.

TITLE: Mother of Parkland school shooting victim pushes for bipartisan legislation after Georgia mass shooting
SUMMARY: Four victims were killed on Sept. 4, 2024, including two students and two teachers, when a lone gunman opened fire at Apalachee High School in Barrow County, Georgia.
